    "recap_headline": "Xavier University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CINCINNATI\n- Xavier baseball fell, 8-5, in the finale of the three-game series against Wofford at Hayden Field on Sunday afternoon.\nThe Musketeers moved to 7-18 on the year, while the Terriers improved to 16-9.\nWofford scored pair in the top of the first, but the\u00a0Musketeers tied it up in the bottom of the frame to send it to the second tied, 2-2.\nJorge Valdes\nled off the inning with a walk,\nClay Burdette\ngot on with a hit-by-pitch, and a single from\nPeter Johnson\nloaded the bases for\nJonathan Fitz\nwho hit a single to right to bring in Valdes.\nJD Crisp\nreached on a fielders choice to bring in Burdette and tie the game.\nXavier moved in front in the second, with\nDonavan Canterberry\ngetting on with a single, moving to second on a bunt from Valdes and coming home on a double from Burdette to make it a 3-2 Xavier lead.\nThe one-run lead held into the fifth, when Wofford scored a pair to take the 4-3 lead, but the Musketeers got the run back in the bottom fo the frame with Burdette hitting a triple and coming home on a single from\nPeter Johnson\nto tie it at 4-4.\nThe Terriers added a pair of runs in both the sixth and the eighth frames to lead 8-4 headed to the bottom of eight.\nLuke Hammond\nled off the frame with a single, moved to third on a double from Canterberry and scored on a sac fly from Valdes, but the Musketeers would get no closer, setting the final score at 8-5.\nXavier returns to Hayden Field on Tuesday, March 24, hosting Cincinnati as part of the Joe Nuxhall Classic. The game with the Bearcats is set to get underway at 3:00 p.m on XAVIER+.\nAT THE PLATE\nClay Burdette\nwent 2-4 at the plate, with a double and a triple, driving in an RBI and scoring two runs.\nJorge Valdes\nfinished 1-2 with a walk, finishing with an RBI and a run scored.\nPeter Johnson\nwent 2-4 with a walk, driving in an RBI.\nJonathan Fitz\nrecorded a pair of hits (2-4) and drove in an RBI.\nJD Crisp\nalso drove in an RBI on a fielder's choice.\nDonavan Canterberry\n(2-4) and\nLuke Hammond\n(1-4) each scored a run.\nCarter Christenson\n(2-5) recorded a pair of hits.\nTommy Townsend\n(1-2) also got on with a hit on a 13-hit day for the Musketeers.\nLandon Mensik\ngot aboard with a walk.\non the mound\nAshton Chronister\nmade the start, going 4.2 innings with four runs allowed on seven hits, striking out three and walking one.\nOwen Poole\nentered with two on and two out in the fifth, going 0.2 innings, allowing two runs on two hits with two walks.\nGarrett Helsel\nentered with one on and one out in the sixth,\u00a0going 2.1 innings, allowing two runs on three hits, walking one and matching his season-high with four strikeouts.\nNick Boyle\nentered with two on and two out in the eighth,\u00a0going 1.0 scoreless inning\u00a0with out allowing a hit, walking one and striking out three.\nJake Hooker\nentered for the final out, getting it with a picked-off base runner.\nVIDEO",
